      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "EVEN BACKWARDS (1) doesn't win out of turn but recent form sound. Has been in the money the last three starts, the latest when third (19.93) at Q Lakeside. Top prospect. FIREBALL ERNIE (2) was safely held in tougher company last start at Townsville, but prior to that won by 0.8 lengths at Townsville (22.09) beating King And I in a Maiden on May 8. Key runner who gets his chance to atone. MIMOSA MOLLY (8) returned a better run last time, finishing in the money (24.43) at this track behind Pookie Bear in a Grade 6. Has the early speed to land on the pace and can stick on. Expected to be in the finish again. DARK END (7) missed the placings here last start but is well-placed to make amends.",
